Idea

Traverse the string from the end:

Skip trailing spaces.
Count characters until you hit a space.

This avoids extra space and is optimal.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)





C++ Code



class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLastWord(string s) {
        int i = s.size() - 1;
        int len = 0;

        while(i >= 0 && s[i] == ' ') i--;

        while(i >= 0 && s[i] != ' '){
            len++;
            i--;
        }

        return len;
    }
};







Example

Input
" fly me to the moon "

Process:

Skip spaces at end
Start counting "moon"

Output

4
Key Insight

Always start from the end → avoids splitting string or extra memory.
